Two separate issues here:

**1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime.** Use `DynamicResource` instead — it re-evaluates when the underlying resource changes.

```xml
<!-- ❌ Won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✅ Updates when you swap the ResourceDictionary -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by replacing the merged dictionary:

```csharp
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

**2. Android restarts your Activity on dark mode change.** By default, Android destroys and recreates the Activity when `uiMode` changes. In your `MainActivity.cs`, add `UiMode` to the `ConfigChanges` attribute:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
        | ConfigChanges.Orientation
        | ConfigChanges.UiMode       // ← prevents restart on dark mode toggle
        | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
        | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

Then detect the system change and react in code:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    bool isDark = e.RequestedTheme == AppTheme.Dark;
    var mergedDicts = Resources.MergedDictionaries;
    mergedDicts.Clear();
    mergedDicts.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
};
```

**TL;DR:** `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` for runtime updates; add `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to prevent Activity recreation.
